    {
      "slug": "wearable-stimulation-system-wss",
      "title": "Wearable Stimulation System (WSS) - COSMIIC Ecosystem",
      "impact": "Architected the open-source WSS software stack for modular functional electrical stimulation hardware, enabling C#, Python, Unity, and ROS 2 applications to control devices through reusable APIs and documentation.",
      "year": "Aug 2025-May 2026",
      "featured": true,
      "tags": [
        "Open source",
        "Research software",
        "Neurotechnology",
        "Functional electrical stimulation",
        "Hardware/software integration",
        "Unity",
        "Python",
        "ROS 2"
      ],
      "role": "Lead software architect and developer / principal contributor. Open-source release and actively maintained research software within the COSMIIC neurotechnology ecosystem.",
      "orgs": [
        "COSMIIC ecosystem",
        "Case Western Reserve University",
        "Human Fusions Institute"
      ],
      "youtubeId": "",
      "outcomes": [
        "Architected and implemented the WSS software stack above the embedded firmware layer.",
        "Built reusable C#, Python, Unity, and ROS 2 integration paths.",
        "Developed stimulation control, transport abstraction, protocol framing, device state handling, setup sequencing, and streaming control.",
        "Implemented serial/test transports, SLIP-like framing, checksums, device addressing, command generation, schedule/event control, and streaming stimulation updates.",
        "Created developer-facing documentation and API reference infrastructure.",
        "Provided documentation that links to the relevant GitHub repositories."
      ],
      "gallery": [],
      "links": [
